WEBVTT

00:01.168 --> 00:02.838
NARRATOR:
In the criminal justice system

00:02.903 --> 00:06.783
the people are represented by two
separate yet equally important groups,

00:06.840 --> 00:08.650
the police
who investigate crime

00:08.709 --> 00:11.519
and the district attorneys
who prosecute the offenders.

00:11.578 --> 00:13.388
These are their stories.

00:14.114 --> 00:17.254
So she turns out the lights and
brings out this big birthday cake.

00:17.317 --> 00:19.227
"Happy Birthday, Harry,"
it says.

00:19.286 --> 00:21.456
How old's the little guy?
Two.

00:21.522 --> 00:24.902
She tried to get him to blow out the candles.
You should have seen that.

00:24.958 --> 00:26.668
Managed to open
his own presents, though.

00:26.727 --> 00:27.727
What'd you get him?

00:27.794 --> 00:30.934
A doghouse, so he'd stop
sleeping in the bed with us.

00:30.998 --> 00:32.567
No such luck.

00:33.267 --> 00:36.707
You know, Shepski, maybe it's time
you two started thinking about kids.

00:36.770 --> 00:40.880
WOMAN ON POLICE RADIO: Any available 2-7
car for a 10-53, possible fatality.

00:40.941 --> 00:42.581
Ambulance en route.

00:43.544 --> 00:46.824
2-7 sector Charlie standing by.
Will respond, Central.

00:47.381 --> 00:48.921
(SIREN WAILING)

00:49.316 --> 00:53.196
1-David-1-0-9-9-9-6-3-6...

00:55.322 --> 00:56.892
CROCKIT: Oh, boy.

00:59.126 --> 01:00.396
It's bad.

01:01.461 --> 01:05.200
2-7 Charlie to Central.
Better put a rush on that bus.

01:07.568 --> 01:11.518
This better be good, Crockit. I was on my way home.
I don't feel so good.

01:11.572 --> 01:13.282
Hey, don't look at me.

01:13.340 --> 01:15.950
AIS guy says there's something
fishy, call the suits.

01:16.009 --> 01:17.609
I do what I'm told.
What happened?

01:17.678 --> 01:20.318
Judging from the skid marks,
this guy's going the wrong way,

01:20.380 --> 01:23.520
swerves into the other car, and wham.
The other guy never had a chance.

01:23.584 --> 01:27.034
Last time I looked I don't
do accident investigations.

01:27.087 --> 01:29.157
(POLICE RADIO CHATTERING)

01:30.190 --> 01:34.730
Here's your murder weapon. Rest
in peace, you sorry bastard.

01:35.028 --> 01:38.068
What the hell happened? Didn't you hear?
We got demoted.

01:38.131 --> 01:40.701
RANDALL: Briscoe, Logan.
Over here.

01:40.767 --> 01:43.907
Randall, this is a traffic accident.
I'm going to bed.

01:43.971 --> 01:47.281
Just take a look at this, would you?
I'm getting ready to write it up.

01:47.341 --> 01:49.621
Looks like a standard 54
with a DOA,

01:49.676 --> 01:53.206
and then I noticed most of her wounds
are on the right side of her body.

01:53.280 --> 01:55.890
Except she's
in the driver's seat.

01:55.949 --> 01:58.229
Yeah. Well,
she's about 5'4 ", 5'2",

01:58.285 --> 02:01.525
but the seat's all the way back and
her feet can't even touch the pedals.

02:01.588 --> 02:03.928
So maybe the seat
got jarred in the crash.

02:03.991 --> 02:06.161
No. It would've
gotten jarred forward.

02:06.226 --> 02:08.466
I don't think she was driving.

02:09.363 --> 02:11.343
So what are you saying?
Somebody moved her?

02:11.398 --> 02:13.108
Then fled the scene.

02:13.166 --> 02:15.646
Not one law-abiding citizen
saw any of this?

02:15.702 --> 02:18.952
A woman down the block says she
heard the crash about 1:45.

02:19.006 --> 02:22.316
That's verified by some people
coming out of Club Mania.

02:22.376 --> 02:24.856
But nobody
actually saw anything.

02:24.911 --> 02:26.891
(SIGHING)
There goes my beauty sleep.

